This may seem like a lot, but its really not that bad. the menuCompilation is used to determine which tab the player is loading, while the selected int is used to tell which skill. This way all skills tabs only work for that skill. Clicking the attack menu sidebar wont open any defence menus like the rest of the shit releases about this.

Then to save you some time converting the code to your server. You can always add this to client.java

[code]private SkillInterfaces skillInterfaces = new SkillInterfaces(this);[/code]
Then add this method somewhere, usually at the bottom
[code]	public SkillInterfaces getSI() {
		return skillInterfaces;
	}[/code]
This way you dont have to convert all my c.getSI(). And thats it, i told you i did it for ease of use, and you will see using it, its very redundant and changeable, all with minimal edits required to anything but the menus. 

